dataset_description.json.Name: Neural representations of others' traits predict social decisions
ReferencesAndLinks: Kobayashi, Kable, Hsu, & Jenkins. (2022). Neural representations of others' traits predict social decisions. PNAS.

Levels.Fixation: Presentation of fixation cross at the beginning of each trial
Levels.Recipient: Presentation of the recipient social group
Levels.Payoff: Presentation of the payoffs. Note the right option was always 10-10
Levels.Timeout: When neither button was pressed within the time limit

selfpay.Description: Payoff for the self in the left option

recipientpay.Description: Payoff for the recipient in the left option

button.Description: Pressed button, L (left) or R (right). NA if no choice was made

README:
This dataset has been published in the following paper:

Kobayashi, K., Kable, J. W., Hsu, M. & Jenkins, A. C. Neural representations of others' traits predict social decisions. PNAS, https://www.pnas.org/doi/10.1073/pnas.2116944119.
 
32 participants completed a modified dictator game paradigm, in which they made eight binary choices on monetary allocation against 20 different recipients with different social group memberships across two scanning runs.

Behavioral data is available at OSF: https://osf.io/qkrhm/.
